    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Reverse Planet Assembly - Disassembly and Assembly</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the one-way clutch pressure plate assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010384" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057691.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse clutch plates.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010385" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057692.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the No. 13 rear reverse planet thrust washer.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010386" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057693.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse clutch ring gear subassembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010387" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057694.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the No. 14 front reverse planet thrust washer.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010388" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057695.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the reverse planet assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>The pins and shafts in the planet assemblies should be checked for loose fit or damage. Use a new
                    planet assembly if either condition exists.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Inspect the pinion gears for damaged or excessively worn teeth.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Check for free rotation of the pinion gears.</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Check for damage in the overdrive planet assembly.</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <figure id="f07010389" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057696.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the No. 15 sun gear thrust bearing.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010390" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0057697.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring. Disassemble the reverse ring gear and hub assembly. Inspect the
                components for damage. If damaged, install new components.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f07010391" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figa00/A0066494.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To assemble, reverse the disassembly procedure.</para>
        </step1>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>Lightly lubricate the thrust bearings with clean automatic transmission fluid to hold them in
                    place during assembly.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>The tabs on the thrust washers must engage the slots on the reverse planet assembly when
                    installed.
                </para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>The snap ring tips must be facing down toward the output shaft hub and fully engaged in the
                    groove.
                </para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
    </svcsubproc>
